    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-head-attention-mechanism-design/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In case, customized binary fingerprint bit locations are not provided within the MSP blocks for training, IDSL_MINT can generate molecular fingerprint descriptors using SMILES or InChI strings for extended connectivity fingerprint (ECFP) using an adjustable radius [19] or MACCS Keys [20] fingerprint types which are widely recognized in the field of cheminformatics [21].",
      "asbval:note": "Paper generates ECFP and MACCS Keys fingerprints but does not explicitly name RDKit as the tool. The paper cites references [19] and [20] for these fingerprint types but does not specify which software library (RDKit, Avalon, or other) is used for generation. The function is present but the specific tool name is not confirmed in the passages.",
