      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "IDSL_MINT was developed using Python 3.10 and implemented with PyTorch 2.0... The IDSL_MINT transformer model architecture for predicting molecular fingerprint is displayed in Figs. 1. IDSL_MINT only takes MS/MS spectra accompanied with precursor m/z values in the.msp text format. First, m/z fragments are tokenized using constant m/z interval steps, and intensity values are sorted by the maximum intensity after normalization to the unit sum of the total intensities.",
