    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-tensor-representation-and-preprocessing/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "IDSL_MINT only takes MS/MS spectra accompanied with precursor m/z values in the.msp text format... IDSL_MINT code is publicly available at https://github.com/idslme/IDSL_MINT... Users can train a new model on these notebooks using the test data or they can use their own input data for creating customized models... Typically, users should specify the criteria for MS/MS spectra input, molecular fingerprint type, transformer model settings, parameters for the cross-entropy LOSS function, and configurations for the Adam optimization strategy.",
      "asbval:note": "IDSL_MINT is confirmed as the framework managing .msp parsing, YAML configuration, and transformer training/inference.",
